data.name: Mac and Cheese Burger
data.quickTastyDescription: A juicy burger topped with creamy mac and cheese for the ultimate indulgent meal!
detailedCookingInstructions: Cook macaroni according to package instructions. Drain and set aside.
In a saucepan, melt butter over medium heat. Stir in flour and cook for 1 minute.
Gradually whisk in milk, cooking until thickened.
Stir in cheddar cheese until melted and smooth. Mix in the cooked macaroni and set aside.
Form ground beef into patties, season with salt, pepper, garlic powder, and onion powder.
Grill or pan-fry the patties over medium-high heat for about 4-5 minutes on each side, or until they reach your desired doneness.
Toast the hamburger buns on the grill or in a toaster.
Assemble the burger: place the beef patty on the bottom bun, top with a generous scoop of mac and cheese, and add optional bacon bits if desired. Close with the top bun.
data.modifiersForBase: Topped with creamy macaroni and cheese
